Pre-requisites

1) Create an account on Git 
2) Install a Git 

Upload your code to git repository

1) Create a new reposity on the Git and copy the url 
2) Go the the project which you want to upload and open the commant prompt from the root of the code
3) git int
4) git add .
5) git commit -m "Initial commit"
5) git remote add origin copiedUrlOfRepository
6) git remote -v (to verify the repository)
7) git push origin master 

Note : if step 7 fails because there is already a file in repository the first pull using below command
git pull --rebase copiedUrlOfRepository

Update files to git repository

1) Make the changes in the code
2) git add .
3) git commit -m "Changes in readme"
4) git push origin master
